    "History": {
      "rows": [
        [
          "Staff Generated Concept",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "Created By:"
        ],
        [
          "A Former Crow scout, Translator, and a Pinkerton,",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "Logan Boese"
        ],
        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "You grew up in a small village in the heart of Crow Country. Born to a family in the Greasy Mouth clan, your childhood was learning how to wrestle with the other boys, hunting, fishing, and tracking. You grew into a fine young man, a proud warrior, had been considered as a medicine man, but instead became a prouder scout and translator. Your natural proclivity to language lead you to work with one of your tribe's newest allies, the United States Armed Forces. You were there at several crucial events. (You were the one who swapped out Sword Bearer's namesake before his fateful battle.) You were a translator and, when that work dried up, a member of the pinkerton detective agency. You were embraced essentially because your sire, a bit of a mad pirate of a man, needed a translator, and felt you, with your interesting history, was an attractive attache to his clan, and more importantly, to his bloodline. Time passed. Things changed. You traveled the world as it changed and it changed you. You often met with other vampires, (especially Gangrel, and even developed a sort of Friendship with several of them.) You met back up with your Sire in Florida, in the late fifties, just in time to realize how far gone he was now. Barely sentient, he had learned things. Dark things. And they'd changed him. He was becoming a problem and threatening a larger reveal of certain secrets of clan and bloodline. He had to be dealt with. You manipulated events to have the Prince call a Blood Hunt on your sire, and you were the one to claim the prize. You took his blood, and with it, his memories. (Which, sort of back fired, since, ever since, he's been appearing to you and whispering dark things, hiding things frm your sight and doing his damnedest to drive you just as mad as he was at the end.) After a long trip in the early nineties, you lay down to sleep, but drifted into Torpor instead. His haven was built over and he only recently awoke, coming back to the world at a time of great change."
        ],
        [
          "Sire:",
          "\"Sir\" Xavier Villory",
          "Reference: (If any)",
          "",
          "",
          "Clan",
          "Malkavians \"Jocastians\" - Permanent Hunger Derangement"
        ],
